#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.123"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.123:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: bharaṇḍuvaggo (bj)
msgctxt "an3.123:0.2"
msgid "13. Kusināravagga"
msgstr "13. Kusināra"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.123:0.3"
msgid "123. Kusinārasutta"
msgstr "123. At Kusināra"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.274"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.123:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kusinārāyaṃ viharati baliharaṇe vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Kusināra, in the Forest of Offerings."

msgctxt "an3.123:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an3.123:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an3.123:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an3.123:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.123:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, take the case of a mendicant living supported by a town or "
"village."

msgctxt "an3.123:2.2"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā upasaṅkamitvā svātanāya bhattena "
"nimanteti."
msgstr ""
"A householder or their child approaches and invites them for tomorrow’s meal."

msgctxt "an3.123:2.3"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu adhivāseti."
msgstr "The mendicant accepts if they want."

msgctxt "an3.123:2.4"
msgid ""
"So tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"tassa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamati; "
"upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdati."
msgstr ""
"When the night has passed, they robe up in the morning, take their bowl and "
"robe, and approach that householder’s home, where they sit on the seat "
"spread out."

msgctxt "an3.123:2.5"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena "
"sahatthā santappeti sampavāreti."
msgstr ""
"The householder or their child serves and satisfies them with their own "
"hands with a variety of delicious foods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.123:3.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "The mendicant thinks:"

msgctxt "an3.123:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu vata myāyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena khādanīyena "
"bhojanīyena sahatthā santappeti sampavāretī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s so good that this householder serves me with a variety of delicious "
"foods.’"

msgctxt "an3.123:3.3"
msgid "Evampissa hoti:"
msgstr "Then they think:"

msgctxt "an3.123:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā āyatimpi evarūpena paṇītena "
"khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappeyya sampavāreyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I really hope this householder serves me with a variety of delicious foods "
"in the future, too.’"

#. VAR: gathito → gadhito (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: ajjhosanno → ajjhāpanno (bj, mr) | ajjhopanno (s1-3, pts1 ṭīkā)
msgctxt "an3.123:3.5"
msgid ""
"So taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ gathito mucchito ajjhosanno anādīnavadassāvī "
"anissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati."
msgstr ""
"They eat that food tied, stupefied, attached, blind to the drawbacks, and "
"not understanding the escape."

msgctxt "an3.123:3.6"
msgid ""
"So tattha kāmavitakkampi vitakketi, byāpādavitakkampi vitakketi, "
"vihiṃsāvitakkampi vitakketi."
msgstr "They think about it with sensual, malicious, or cruel thoughts."

msgctxt "an3.123:3.7"
msgid "Evarūpassāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno dinnaṃ na mahapphalanti vadāmi."
msgstr "A gift to such a mendicant is not very fruitful, I say."

msgctxt "an3.123:3.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.123:3.9"
msgid "Pamatto hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu viharati."
msgstr "Because that mendicant is negligent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.123:4.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya "
"viharati."
msgstr "Take another case of a mendicant living supported by a town or village."

msgctxt "an3.123:4.2"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā upasaṅkamitvā svātanāya bhattena "
"nimanteti."
msgstr ""
"A householder or their child approaches and invites them for tomorrow’s meal."

msgctxt "an3.123:4.3"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu adhivāseti."
msgstr "The mendicant accepts if they want."

msgctxt "an3.123:4.4"
msgid ""
"So tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"tassa gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkamati; "
"upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdati."
msgstr ""
"When the night has passed, they robe up in the morning, take their bowl and "
"robe, and approach that householder’s home, where they sit on the seat "
"spread out."

msgctxt "an3.123:4.5"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena "
"sahatthā santappeti sampavāreti."
msgstr ""
"The householder or their child serves and satisfies them with their own "
"hands with a variety of delicious foods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.275"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.123:5.1"
msgid "Tassa na evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "It never occurs to them:"

msgctxt "an3.123:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu vata myāyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena khādanīyena "
"bhojanīyena sahatthā santappeti sampavāretī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s so good that the householder or their child serves and satisfies me "
"with their own hands with a variety of delicious foods.’"

msgctxt "an3.123:5.3"
msgid "Evampissa na hoti:"
msgstr "They don’t think:"

msgctxt "an3.123:5.4"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā āyatimpi evarūpena paṇītena "
"khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappeyya sampavāreyyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I really hope this householder serves me with a variety of delicious foods "
"in the future, too.’"

msgctxt "an3.123:5.5"
msgid ""
"So taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ agathito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī "
"nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati."
msgstr ""
"They eat that alms-food untied, unstupefied, unattached, seeing the "
"drawback, and understanding the escape."

msgctxt "an3.123:5.6"
msgid ""
"So tattha nekkhammavitakkampi vitakketi, abyāpādavitakkampi vitakketi, "
"avihiṃsāvitakkampi vitakketi."
msgstr "They think about it with thoughts of renunciation, love, or kindness."

msgctxt "an3.123:5.7"
msgid "Evarūpassāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno dinnaṃ mahapphalanti vadāmi."
msgstr "A gift to such a mendicant is very fruitful, I say."

msgctxt "an3.123:5.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.123:5.9"
msgid "Appamatto hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu viharatī”ti."
msgstr "Because that mendicant is diligent.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.123:5.10"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
